The paper deals with fundamental problems in reinforcement learning, including exploration-exploitation trade-offs, optimality, and partial observability. These topics are central to machine learning and artificial intelligence, which suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are likely categories. The paper also discusses information theory and multi-agent environments, which could place it in cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems). Finally, the paper presents results on Nash equilibria, which suggests that it could be relevant to cs.GT (Game Theory).
